    {
      "element_id": "sec-a-23",
      "element_type": "section",
      "paragraph_ref": "A-23",
      "title": "A-23 Maximum Allowable Stress Values",
      "content": "(a) The maximum allowable stress values for materials used in the construction of pressure vessels shall be taken from Part M of this Standard. Specifically, allowable stress values for carbon and low-alloy steels shall be obtained from Table M-1 (see Part M).\n\n(b) Allowable stress values are tabulated at discrete design temperatures. When a design tem-perature falls between two tabulated values, linear interpolation shall be used, in accordance with A-23(c).\n\n(c) No extrapolation beyond the tabulated temperature range is permitted. If the design temper-ature exceeds the maximum tabulated temperature for a material, that material shall not be used.",
      "page_number": 1,
      "parent_id": null,
      "cross_references": [
        {
          "source_id": "sec-a-23",
          "target_id": "tbl-m-1",
          "reference_text": "shall be obtained from Table M-1",
          "reference_type": "references"
        }
      ],
      "table": null,
      "formula": null,
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "element_id": "sec-a-25",
      "element_type": "section",
      "paragraph_ref": "A-25",
      "title": "A-25 Corrosion",
      "content": "(a) A corrosion allowance (CA) shall be added to the minimum required thickness calculated by A-27 or A-32.\n\n(b) The corrosion allowance shall be specified in the design datasheet and shall not be taken as less than zero.\n\n(c) When back-calculating the Maximum Allowable Working Pressure (MAWP), the effective cor-roded thickness equals the nominal thickness minus the corrosion allowance.",
      "page_number": 1,
      "parent_id": null,
      "cross_references": [
        {
          "source_id": "sec-a-25",
          "target_id": "sec-a-27",
          "reference_text": "A-27",
          "reference_type": "references"
        },
        {
          "source_id": "sec-a-25",
          "target_id": "sec-a-32",
          "reference_text": "A-32",
          "reference_type": "references"
        }
      ],
      "table": null,
      "formula": null,
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "element_id": "sec-a-27",
      "element_type": "section",
      "paragraph_ref": "A-27",
      "title": "A-27 Thickness of Shells Under Internal Pressure",
      "content": "(a) The minimum required thickness of shells subjected to internal pressure shall not be less than that computed by the following formulas, per A-27(c) and A-27(d).\n\n(b) The allowable stress S shall be obtained per A-23, and the joint efficiency E shall be obtained from Table B-12 (see B-12).\n\n(c) Cylindrical Shells.\n\nA-27(c)(1) Inside Radius Formula: -\n\nt = (P × R) / (S × E − 0.6 × P)\n\nwhere:\n\n• t = minimum required thickness, mm\n\n• P = design pressure, MPa\n\n• R = inside radius of the shell course, mm\n\n• S = maximum allowable stress at design temperature, MPa (see Table M-1)\n\n1\n\n• E = joint efficiency (see Table B-12)\n\nThis formula applies when: t ≤ R/2 AND P ≤ 0.385 × S × E. When these conditions are not satisfied, the rules of A-27(c)(3) shall be applied (not covered here).",
      "page_number": 1,
      "parent_id": null,
      "cross_references": [
        {
          "source_id": "sec-a-27",
          "target_id": "sec-a-23",
          "reference_text": "per A-23",
          "reference_type": "references"
        },
        {
          "source_id": "sec-a-27",
          "target_id": "tbl-b-12",
          "reference_text": "shall be obtained from Table B-12",
          "reference_type": "references"
        },
        {
          "source_id": "sec-a-27",
          "target_id": "tbl-m-1",
          "reference_text": "see Table M-1",
          "reference_type": "references"
        }
      ],
      "table": null,
      "formula": null,
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "element_id": "sec-a-27",
      "element_type": "section",
      "paragraph_ref": "A-27",
      "title": "A-27(c)(2) — Outside Radius Formula:",
      "content": "t = (P × Ro) / (S × E + 0.4 × P)\n\nwhere Ro is the outside radius of the shell course. Applicable when P ≤ 0.385 × S × E.\n\n(d) Spherical Shells.",
      "page_number": 2,
      "parent_id": null,
      "cross_references": [],
      "table": null,
      "formula": null,
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "element_id": "sec-a-27",
      "element_type": "section",
      "paragraph_ref": "A-27",
      "title": "A-27(d) — Spherical Shell Formula:",
      "content": "t = (P × R) / (2 × S × E − 0.2 × P)\n\nApplicable when t ≤ 0.356 × R AND P ≤ 0.665 × S × E.",
      "page_number": 2,
      "parent_id": null,
      "cross_references": [],
      "table": null,
      "formula": null,
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "element_id": "sec-a-32",
      "element_type": "section",
      "paragraph_ref": "A-32",
      "title": "A-32 Formed Heads",
      "content": "Formed heads (ellipsoidal, torispherical, hemispherical, conical) are covered by this paragraph. For a 2:1 ellipsoidal head:\n\nt = (P × D) / (2 × S × E − 0.2 × P)\n\nwhere D is the inside diameter. The joint efficiency E shall be taken from Table B-12 and the allowable stress S from Table M-1 per A-23.",
      "page_number": 2,
      "parent_id": null,
      "cross_references": [
        {
          "source_id": "sec-a-32",
          "target_id": "tbl-b-12",
          "reference_text": "shall be taken from Table B-12",
          "reference_type": "references"
        },
        {
          "source_id": "sec-a-32",
          "target_id": "tbl-m-1",
          "reference_text": "from Table M-1",
          "reference_type": "references"
        },
        {
          "source_id": "sec-a-32",
          "target_id": "sec-a-23",
          "reference_text": "per A-23",
          "reference_type": "references"
        }
      ],
      "table": null,
      "formula": null,
      "metadata": {}
    },
