    {
      "element_id": "sec-b-12",
      "element_type": "section",
      "paragraph_ref": "B-12",
      "title": "B-12 Joint Efficiency",
      "content": "(a) The joint efficiency E used in the thickness formulas of A-27 and A-32 shall be taken from Table B-12 as a function of the joint type (Types 1 through 6) and the extent of radiographic examination (Full RT, Spot RT, or None).\n\n(b) Table B-12 — Joint Efficiency Values:\n\n| Joint Type   | Description                               | Full RT   | Spot RT   | No RT   |\n|-|-|-|-|-|\n| 1            | Double-welded butt, full penetration      | 1.00      | 0.85      | 0.70    |\n| 2            | Single-welded butt with backing strip     | 0.90      | 0.80      | 0.65    |\n| 3            | Single-welded butt without backing        | 0.80      | 0.70      | 0.60    |\n| 4            | Double full-fillet lap                    | 0.75      | 0.65      | 0.55    |\n| 5            | Single full-fillet lap with plug welds    | 0.70      | 0.60      | 0.50    |\n| 6            | Single full-fillet lap without plug welds | 0.65      | 0.55      | 0.45    |\n\n(c) The radiography level selected shall be consistent with the service conditions and shall be documented.\n\n2",
      "page_number": 2,
      "parent_id": null,
      "cross_references": [
        {
          "source_id": "sec-b-12",
          "target_id": "tbl-b-12",
          "reference_text": "shall be taken from Table B-12",
          "reference_type": "references"
        },
        {
          "source_id": "sec-b-12",
          "target_id": "sec-a-27",
          "reference_text": "A-27",
          "reference_type": "references"
        },
        {
          "source_id": "sec-b-12",
          "target_id": "sec-a-32",
          "reference_text": "A-32",
          "reference_type": "references"
        }
      ],
      "table": null,
